Subject: 4.[123]bsd vi lets careless users lock ttys, waste administrators' time

Index: ucb/vi 4.2BSD

Description:
	Careless users can, using vi, lock their terminals.

Repeat-By:
	Type the following:
		vi
		:map G 0Ga
		G
	Then find another terminal to unlock your terminal from (or do what
	folks here do--bug the nearest administrator).
